Root Directory
The directory within your project, where your code is located. Leave this field empty if your code is not located in a subdirectory.


Include files outside the root directory in the Build Step.

Skip deployments when there are no changes to the root directory or its dependencies.

Learn more about Root Directory
Ignored Build Step
When a commit is pushed to the Git repository that is connected with your Project, its SHA will determine if a new Build has to be issued. If the SHA was deployed before, no new Build will be issued.

You can customize this behavior with a command that exits with code 1 (new Build needed) or code 0.

